The paper deals with algebraic language theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. The use of monads and duality suggests a connection to category theory, which is often used in logic and semantics. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with languages of finite and infinite words and trees, which suggests a connection to formal languages (cs.FL). The use of pseudovarieties of finite algebras suggests a connection to algebraic structures (cs.DM). The paper also mentions a variety theorem, which suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT).
